Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Trim, then thinly slice @button mushrooms{8}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Strip @thyme{¼%ounce}(leaves stripped from stems) from stems; discard stems. Roughly chop leaves. Finely chop @parsley{¼%ounce}(chopped). Slice half the @polenta{½%tube} into ½-inch rounds (use the rest as you like).

Heat a thin layer of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat (we used 1 TBSP). Add polenta and cook until browned and crisp on surface, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #baking sheet{} and place in oven to keep warm.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, tossing, until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add shallot, thyme, and garlic. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Pour in @water{½%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and let simmer until reduced to a saucy consistency, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat. Stir in @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce}, @pine nuts{1%ounce}, @balsamic vinegar{2%teaspoon}, and a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide polenta between plates. Spoon over gravy. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup} and parsley. Add salad to the side and serve.